{
  "answer": "**Chapter 11 of Allama Iqbal's *Bang-E-Dara Part 1* is titled \"Sakhtiyan karta hoon dil par, ghair se ghafil hoon main\"** (which is itself the *matla*, or opening couplet, of this ghazal-style poem).[^1]\n\nThe *matla*'s claim is a self-description by the speaker: \"I impose hardships upon my heart; from others, I remain heedless.\" In English translation: \"...I am harsh upon my heart; of all else, heedless I am.\" This sets the tone for the poem's repeated refrain of paradoxical self-identification (\"main\" / \"I am\").[^2][^3]\n\n[^1]: *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, ch. 11, [chapter](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/11-sakhtiyan-karta-hoon-dil-par-ghair-se-ghafil-hoon-/translation/).\n\n[^2]: *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, ch. 11, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/11-sakhtiyan-karta-hoon-dil-par-ghair-se-ghafil-hoon-/translation/#p-941acb).\n\n[^3]: Poem metadata from chapter listing.[^list_chapters]",
